foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The number of requests pending at the start of the fiscal year is sixteen lower for FAA, one lower for FHWA, one lower for MARAD, three lower for NHTSA, and nine lower for PHMSA. The adjustment reflects requests where all final action was taken in FY 2013, but not all database closures were entered in FY 2013.

The number of requests pending at the start of the fiscal year is one higher for FMCSA that reported in last year's report. The adjustment reflects requests that were received at the end of FY 2013, but not logged until FY 2014.
For the reasons stated above, the number of requests pending at the start of the fiscal year for the agency overall is 29 lower than reported in last year's report.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The number of pending appeals at the start of the fiscal year for FAA is three higher than reported in last year's report. This adjustment is due to three appeals that were received in FY 2013, but not logged until FY 2014.

The number of pending appeals at the start of the fiscal year for FTA is one lower than reported in last year's report. This adjustment is due to one appeal that was closed in FY 2013, but not logged out until FY 2014.
For the reasons stated above, the number pending at the start of the FY for the agency overall is two higher than reported in last year's report.
